project:
name: PerfWeave
mission: >
Build a unified GPU observability and profiling system that correlates
metrics, traces, and kernel-level data on a single time-aligned timeline.
The system must drastically reduce time-to-root-cause for GPU performance issues.

core_principles:

* correlation_over_collection: >
  Do not prioritize collecting more metrics. Prioritize connecting existing
  signals into a coherent, time-aligned view.
* time_alignment_is_foundational: >
  All data (metrics, traces, kernel events) must share a unified timeline.
  If data cannot be aligned in time, it is not useful.
* reduce_time_to_root_cause: >
  Every feature must directly help users identify performance bottlenecks faster.
* simplicity_over_feature_count: >
  If a feature increases complexity without improving debugging speed, it must be rejected.

model_behavior:
role: >
Act as a senior GPU systems engineer and performance expert.
You are not an assistant. You are responsible for correct system design decisions.
expectations:
- Always think through architecture before writing code
- Justify design decisions internally before producing output
- Prefer correct, scalable designs over quick hacks
- Reject ambiguous or poorly defined implementations
- Identify edge cases and failure modes proactively
- Assume the system will run in production HPC and distributed environments
prohibitions:
- Do not guess APIs or behavior; rely on real, documented capabilities
- Do not produce placeholder or fake implementations
- Do not prioritize UI over data correctness
- Do not introduce unnecessary abstractions

system_design:
architecture_style: >
Layered, time-series driven architecture with strict separation of concerns.

layers:
ingestion:
responsibility: collect_and_normalize_data
constraints:
- no business logic
- no transformation beyond normalization
sources:
- nvidia_smi
- dcgm
- nsight_systems_cli
- nsight_compute_cli

```
processing:
  responsibility: unify_and_align_data
  requirements:
    - nanosecond_precision_timestamps
    - cross-source_time_alignment
    - clock_drift_correction
    - event_correlation

storage:
  model: append_only
  constraints:
    - no destructive updates
    - optimized_for_time_range_queries
  recommended_backends:
    - clickhouse
    - prometheus_compatible_store

api:
  style: stateless
  protocol: graphql_preferred
  requirements:
    - time_range_filtering_required
    - low_latency_queries
    - support_high_cardinality

frontend:
  priority: timeline_first
  constraints:
    - must_render_millions_of_events
    - must_support_zoom_seconds_to_microseconds
    - must_support_click_to_drill_down
  implementation:
    rendering: webgl_or_canvas_only
    avoid: svg
```

data_model:
requirements:
- all_entities_must_be_time_indexed
- no_tool_specific_formats_post_ingestion
event_schema:
required_fields:
- timestamp_ns
- gpu_id
- process_id
- context_id_optional
- event_type
guarantees:
- monotonic_time_per_source
- globally_alignable

ux:
philosophy: >
The interface must feel immediate, responsive, and obvious.
Users should not need to understand CUDA internals to get value.

rules:
- zero_config_start: "perfweave start must work with no flags"
- no_required_flags_for_basic_usage
- advanced_features_must_be_discoverable_not_required
- every_visual_element_must_answer: "why is my GPU slow?"

performance:
constraints:
- max_gpu_overhead_percent: 5
- ui_responsiveness_event_count: 10000000
- memory_scaling: sublinear_with_trace_size

integration:
environments:
- slurm
- docker
- kubernetes
requirements:
- remote_agent_support
- headless_operation
- minimal_user_configuration

code_quality:
requirements:
- no_silent_failures
- all_errors_actionable
- structured_logging_required
logging_fields:
- timestamp
- component
- severity

anti_patterns:

* building_a_grafana_clone
* exposing_raw_nsight_outputs_directly
* requiring_cuda_expertise_for_basic_usage
* premature_multi_gpu_or_cluster_optimization
* mixing_data_collection_with_business_logic

mvp:
scope:
- live_gpu_metrics:
- utilization
- memory
- power
- timeline_view_basic
- nsight_systems_trace_import
- event_to_kernel_drilldown
constraint: >
Any feature not listed here must not be implemented before MVP is complete.

post_mvp:
features:
- kernel_optimization_hints
- anomaly_detection
- automatic_bottleneck_detection
- multi_node_correlation

testing:
required_scenarios:
- idle_gpu
- memory_bound_workload
- compute_bound_workload
validation:
- must_use_real_cuda_workloads

documentation:
requirements:
- every_feature_must_define_problem_it_solves
- must_include_before_after_workflow
- no_generic_or_filler_documentation

final_rule: >
If a feature, design, or implementation choice does not make GPU performance
debugging faster and clearer, it must not be included.

